### Example 3: Requirements Gathering - Notification System Design
POST {{AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT}}openai/deployments/{{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_DEPLOYMENT_NAME}}/chat/completions?api-version={{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_API_VERSION}}
Content-Type: application/json
api-key: {{AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY}}

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I need to build a notification system for our app."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'll help you design a notification system. Let's start by understanding your requirements:\n\n1. What types of notifications? (push, email, SMS, in-app)\n2. Expected volume of notifications?\n3. Real-time requirements?\n4. Target platforms? (web, mobile, both)\n5. Any compliance requirements?"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We need email and push notifications. Probably 50,000 notifications per day. Real-time is important for some alerts. Both web and mobile. We're in healthcare so HIPAA compliance is required."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a HIPAA-compliant notification system handling 50k daily notifications with real-time requirements, here's my initial assessment:\n\n**Key Considerations:**\n- HIPAA requires end-to-end encryption and audit logs\n- No PHI in notification content\n- Secure storage of notification history\n\n**Architecture Questions:**\n1. What's your current tech stack?\n2. Do you have preference for cloud providers?\n3. Budget constraints?\n4. Do you need notification templates?\n5. Required delivery guarantees?"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We use .NET Core with React. Already on Azure. Budget is flexible for the right solution. Yes, we need templates for consistent messaging. At-least-once delivery is required for critical alerts."
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 1200,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

