### Example 4: Learning User Preferences - Code Style Adaptation
POST {{AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT}}openai/deployments/{{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_DEPLOYMENT_NAME}}/chat/completions?api-version={{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_API_VERSION}}
Content-Type: application/json
api-key: {{AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY}}

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Show me how to connect to a database in Python."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'll show you how to connect to a database in Python. Which database system are you using? (PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, MongoDB, etc.)"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "PostgreSQL"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's how to connect to PostgreSQL in Python using psycopg2:\n\n```python\nimport psycopg2\nfrom psycopg2 import sql\n\n# Connection parameters\nconn = psycopg2.connect(\n    host=\"localhost\",\n    database=\"your_database\",\n    user=\"your_username\",\n    password=\"your_password\",\n    port=\"5432\"\n)\n\n# Create a cursor\ncur = conn.cursor()\n\n# Execute a query\ncur.execute(\"SELECT * FROM users LIMIT 5\")\nrows = cur.fetchall()\n\nfor row in rows:\n    print(row)\n\n# Close connections\ncur.close()\nconn.close()\n```\n\nDo you prefer using an ORM like SQLAlchemy, or raw SQL queries?"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I prefer SQLAlchemy. Also, I always use environment variables for credentials and async operations when possible."
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 1000,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

