### Example 5: Customer Support Context Building
POST {{AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT}}openai/deployments/{{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_DEPLOYMENT_NAME}}/chat/completions?api-version={{AZURE_OPENAI_GPT4O_API_VERSION}}
Content-Type: application/json
api-key: {{AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY}}

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm having trouble with my account."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm here to help you with your account issue. To assist you better, could you please tell me:\n1. What specific problem are you experiencing?\n2. What service or application is this related to?\n3. When did you first notice this issue?"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I can't log into my cloud storage account. It says my password is wrong, but I'm sure it's correct. This started this morning."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand how frustrating login issues can be. Let's troubleshoot this step by step:\n\n1. Have you tried using the 'Forgot Password' option to reset it?\n2. Are you seeing any specific error messages beyond \"wrong password\"?\n3. Are you trying to log in from the same device/browser you normally use?\n4. Have you recently changed your password or enabled two-factor authentication?\n\nAlso, to better assist you, which cloud storage service are you using? (Google Drive, Dropbox, OneDrive, etc.)"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It's OneDrive. I haven't tried password reset yet. The exact error is 'Sign-in failed. Please check your credentials.' I'm using Chrome on my work laptop like always. We did have a company-wide security update last week."
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 1000,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

###

# 💡 Multi-Turn Context Best Practices:
#
# 1. Progressive Disclosure: Gather information naturally through conversation
# 2. Maintain Context: Reference previous messages to show understanding
# 3. Ask Clarifying Questions: Don't assume, ask for specifics
# 4. Summarize Periodically: Confirm understanding of gathered context
# 5. Adapt Responses: Tailor advice based on accumulated knowledge
#
# Advantages:
# - Dynamic context building
# - Natural conversation flow
# - Can handle complex, evolving scenarios
# - User controls information disclosure
# - Flexible for exploratory interactions
#
# Limitations:
# - Context window limits (older messages may be truncated)
# - More tokens used for conversation history
# - Requires multiple API calls
# - Context lost between sessions unless saved
